# maintain_suite

The 10-fixture v1 acceptance bench. Strict gates dispatch through a
single pipeline; new fixtures must declare their per-requirement spec.

## Must
- `vacuous_test` gate fires on `implement` + `tests_pass` only
- `min_added_lines` is a floor, not a ceiling
- New fixtures land with a `requirements:` block (SpecDD Lever 1 schema)
- Bench runs use `--work-dir ~/.llamabench/bench-workspace` (variance leak fix)
- Sidecar regrade via `scripts/regrade_local.py` re-runs the citation linter against `synthesizer.md`
- Borderline document/manage fixtures replicate 3× before claiming a regression

## Must not
- Run bench without `--keep-loaded` (post-run unload fires by default)
- Trust `scripts/regrade_local.py` results that read `origin/<branch>` (pre-v1.4.1 bug; fixed but stay alert)
- Add fixtures without `task_type` in the YAML (cve_lookup gating depends on it)

## Owns
- benchmarks/maintain_suite/**
